OL,3,CNon-ministers spend #35,000 of
OL,4,Ctaxpayers' money on global trips
OL,6,FMore than #35,000 was spent on non-
OL,7,Fministerial politicians attending
OL,8,Fevents off-island as part of Jersey's
OL,9,FCommonwealth Parliamentary Association
OL,10,Fin 2023.
OL,12,FThe costs include visits to Kenya,
OL,13,FGhana and Canada.
OL,15,FThe group's chair, Deputy Rob Ward,
OL,16,Fsays these trips strengthen
OL,17,Frelationships abroad and offer local
OL,18,Frepresentatives the chance to discuss
OL,19,Fimportant issues with others from
OL,20,Facross the globe.
